Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Anne Armstrong appointed London envoy
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03z98ht
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 11 Jan 1976
Former Nixon aide, Republican Anne Armstrong, appointed as US ambassador to the UK. This archive edition of Letter from America was recorded by one of two listeners, who between them taped and labelled over 650 Letter From America programmes from 1973 to 1989. It was restored by the BBC in 2014.